As part of activities to mark this year’s Valentine, Abuja real estate developers, T Pumpy on Thursday, pampered her subscribers with the screening of the movie, Survival of Jelili. The Genesis Cinema movie hall was filled to capacity with overflow of T.Pumpy estate subscribers and their spouses. Speaking on the development, MD CEO of the company, Tayo Adaralegbe said, “Valentine is to celebrate love, so we have brought subscribers and their loved ones to the cinemas to celebrate love and we are doing another one in Easter and Sallah.”  Nollywod star, Femi Adebayo, who spoke shortly before the screening of the movie, thanked T Pumpy Concept Limited and others who made it possible. Other subscribers, who spoke with newsmen at the movie screening, thanked T.Pumpy for what they described as first of it’s kind gesture by any developer. Meanwhile, the ongoing promo is still on.  The CEO had announced in January that the company has slashed the price of its 4/5 bedroom duplex land sales with massive discounts. According to him, the estate land, which is government approved, has about 650sqm for 4 or 5 bedroom duplex or penthouse or can be used for 4-bedroom standard bungalow. He said the market value of the land is N3m, however, the company is giving out 20 percent discount, which is N600,000 and 2,020 blocks, which is valued at N380,000.  “Total value discount is N980,000 off 3,000,000 which is 2,020,000. Pay 2,020,000 the land is yours,” he said. The T-Pumpy Concept team have decades of providing industry-acclaimed off-site home designs and constructions. Whether you’re interested in a manufactured home or an innovative modular design, the T-Pumpy Concept team continues to deliver what home buyers are looking for in their new homes along with the quality construction they expect and deserve.  Corporate Office address: No. 12, Monrovia Street, Off Aminu Kano Crescent, Wuse II district, Abuja Annex House 23, (F) Road, Beside RCCG Resurrection Parish, FHA Lugbe, Abuja.  Fo